Nguyen Trung Duc is an Intern Backend Developer with 0 years of commercial experience. Their core expertise encompasses designing and implementing robust **RESTful APIs** and **Microservices Architecture**, with a strong focus on **JWT authentication**, **user authentication**, **horizontal scaling**, and **load balancing** using **Nginx**. Through academic and group projects, Duc has demonstrated proficiency in backend development, notably building a **Spring Boot** and **MySQL**-based vocabulary platform leveraging **JPA**, **Hibernate**, **Spring Mail** for **email notifications**, and **PDF/Word generation**, ensuring **code quality** with **JUnit** and **Mockito** testing. They also contributed to a full-stack E-commerce platform utilizing **Node.js/Express**, **MongoDB**, and **Redis** in a **Microservices Architecture**, where they containerized services with **Docker** and implemented **product management** and **shopping cart features**.
Technically, Nguyen Trung Duc is proficient in **JavaScript**, **Java**, **Python**, and **C/C++**. Their hands-on experience extends to backend frameworks like **Node.js** and **Spring Boot**, including **Express**, **JPA**, **Hibernate**, and **Spring Mail**. For frontend, they have worked with **React.js (Vite)**, **EJS**, and **Bootstrap**. Duc is skilled in database management with **MySQL**, **MongoDB**, **MS SQL Server**, and **Redis**. In DevOps and cloud, they have practical experience with **Docker** for containerization, **Nginx** for reverse proxy and load balancing, and basic cloud deployments on **AWS (EC2)**, alongside local server environments like **XAMPP**. Additional tools include **Swagger** for API documentation, **Git** for version control, and **Postman** for API testing. Their conceptual understanding includes **OOP** principles, **code quality** practices, and practical application of techniques such as **email notifications**, **PDF generation**, and **Word generation**.